Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1058
H.P. 687 House of Representatives, March 14, 2025
Coverage When Other Insurance Is Involved
Received by the Clerk of the House on March 12, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Health Coverage, Insurance and Financial Services pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered
printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative GREENWOOD of Wales.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 24-A MRSA ยง2723-A, sub-ยง4 is enacted to read:
3 4. Coordination of benefits for dental insurance. Notwithstanding subsection 1, a
4 policy may not coordinate benefits when an insured is covered under more than one policy
5 that provides benefits for dental services.
6 SUMMARY
77 This bill prohibits the coordination of benefits when an insured is covered under more
88 than one policy that provides benefits for dental services.
